ABUJA &#8211; Nigeria has increased its oil production to 2.1 million barrels a day, its oil minister said on Tuesday.&#8220;Current production&#8230;today is 2.1 million as a result of ongoing dialogues,&#8221; Emmanuel Ibe Kachikwu told reporters. He put production at 1.8 million bpd last week.He spoke after President Muhammadu Buhari and other top officials met leaders and militant representatives from the Niger Delta to end militant attacks on oil pipelines in the oil hub.